title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith and Wesson M&P Performance Center PC15-1
postcontent:
This is Smith and Wesson's first version of the Peformance Center on the AR15 Platform. It is top quality through and through. This Smith & Wesson's M&P 15PC-1 from the Performance Center is one of the top choice for any serious shooter, and very hard to find. This earlier model is superior than the current model on the receiver and stock. This S&W Performance Center M&P 15PC-1 has a 20‚Äù Stainless Steel barrel, Chromed Bolt Carrier, Two-Stage compitition trigger, Hard Coat black anodized finish from the factory.

 I use this rifle for hunting coyote sometimes, but mostly use it for varmit (Despite what Obama says about people using AR's for hunting), It has earned such nickname's as the "Black Death" and "Nail Driver" amongst my friends. The accuracy is second to none, it is almost boring to shoot because I can hold a dime size group at 100 yards all day with it. So unless you're using it to shoot 2-3" targets at 150-200 yards it's boring at the range lol. 

 I am a U.S. Marine so needless to say the weapon has been well taken care of. It is in peak condition mechanically, but shows signs of use. As I said, I have not bought it to sit in a safe and collect dust, I bought it to be a deadly accurate weapon system, and that it is. If you're looking for a unfired weapon or a weapon to sit in a safe and collect dust then please move on because this is not what you're looking for. However, if you're looking for a field tested and true'd weapon, that has this U.S. Marine's approval; this is it. 

 Now to the price... When the weapon hit the market the MSRP was $2750 for the bare rifle. That means no optics and no bipod. 

 Add on's include:
 -Magpul PRS Stock $300 (if you can find one) 
 -UTG MilDot Scope with Red/Green lit reticle $150 (High dollar scopes are for scout snipers, and gear queers that hope it will make them shoot better. Yeah, I said it... If you doubt me, then put your money where your mouth is. I will out shoot you all day with this $150 scope vs. your $2000 glass that doesn't help your shot placement.)
 -Magpul Quarter Turn Iron Sights (For targets <50 yards) 
 -UTG Bipod, Tactical Charging Handle (less tactical, more practicle to get around the optics), and a Tactical Mag release (Again, Less tactical, more practical)

 I also have a ton of G.I. Mags and 5.56 Ammo that can be negotiated for. Please feel free to contact me with questions and/or offers.

Rough Rider ... the very image conjured up is of the rugged men led by Theodore Roosevelt up Kettle Hill and San Juan Hill over 100 years ago during our war with Spain. That same image of ruggedness might also be applied to the newest Big Bore Rough Rider revolver from Heritage. Almost the "spitting image" of the Single Action Army still be carried by some troops during the Spanish-American War, this latest six-shooter comes chambered for the legendary .45 Colt cartridge, .44-40 and .357 Magnum. This fine handgun can be had in the traditional 4.75", 5.5" and 7.5" barrel lengths, just like the original. Blue, nickel, stainless and blue/color-case hardened finishes are available and each gun is fitted with attractive one-piece cocobolo grips. The action features a frame mounted inertia firing pin and transfer bar for added protection. Old World gun maker Pietta of Italy start certain parts for us. They are a family run operation, just like Heritage Manufacturing. Then those certain parts are finished by Heritage, then plated then fully assembled by us in the good old US.

title: For Sale:  Red Ryder BB Gun
postcontent:
-0.177 caliber airgun with smooth bore, steel barrel
-Stained solid wood stock and forearm; blade and ramp front sight; adjustable rear sight
-Lever-cocking, spring air action
-Shoots up to 350 feet per second; 650 shot capacity
-Recommended for ages 10 and older with adult supervision

The Red Ryder BB Gun is a lever-action, spring piston air gun with a smooth bore barrel, adjustable iron sights, and a gravity feed magazine with a 650 BB capacity. It differs from the standard Daisy lever action BB guns by the addition of an engraved stock, and a saddle ring with leather thong on the receiver. A youth model airgun, the BB gun produces velocities of about 280 feet per second (85 m/s), though on newer models it says it is capable of shooting at 350 feet per second (110 m/s) with standard steel BBs. This has been proven true, and newer models usually retain 375 ft/s (114 m/s) velocity. The effective range is fairly short, about 10 yards (9 m), after which the low velocity and inaccuracy of the smooth bore barrel makes hitting the target difficult. BB guns are shot competitively at distances of 5 yards (4.5 m), but the rudimentary open sights on the Red Ryder make it impractical for competition, and it is primarily a plinking airgun.
